The code for the following plugin provides an implementation that generates 
DFXML output - see:
  http://www.forensicswiki.org/wiki/Category:Digital_Forensics_XML
and:
  http://www.forensicswiki.org/wiki/Digital_Forensics_XML_Schema
for more information.

To install this plugins simply include it (e.g. with the --plugins command 
line option), when running Volatility 2.0.

  exportfile.py - this plugin implements the exporting and saving of 
                  _FILE_OBJECT's by exporting file page data in a DFXML format.

File reconstruction functionality is achieved using Python code and the dfxml.py 
file in the fiwalk package.

CURRENT LIMITATION
==================

In order to use this plugin, it is necessary to use Volatility r1145 or latter.

For libmagic functionality, you'll also need to ensure python-magic is installed.